1
00:01:10,080 --> 00:01:10,640
Qiming,

2
00:01:12,120 --> 00:01:13,520
regarding my promotion,

3
00:01:13,880 --> 00:01:15,520
what exactly did you do?

4
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:19,000
I just wanted to help you move up.

5
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:21,320
But I told you not to.

6
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:23,080
Don't be so stubborn.

7
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:25,720
I told you. Just trust me.

8
00:01:26,280 --> 00:01:29,080
I don't want to rely on connections or buy my way up.

9
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:31,039
But we need you.

10
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:32,800
Once you take office,

11
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:34,880
just do your job fairly and justly.

12
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:36,729
And we'll run our business.

13
00:01:36,880 --> 00:01:39,080
I just want to clear up this muddy water.

14
00:01:39,680 --> 00:01:40,479
Oh, you.

15
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:42,160
For this promotion,

16
00:01:42,160 --> 00:01:43,880
someone recommended another person,

17
00:01:43,880 --> 00:01:45,759
but I was the one publicly announced.

18
00:01:45,759 --> 00:01:47,090
What will others think?

19
00:01:47,960 --> 00:01:49,400
You didn't do anything, so what are you afraid of?

20
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:50,800
Let them think whatever.

21
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:53,860
What about the rebar incident this time?

22
00:01:56,600 --> 00:01:57,920
I have nothing to hide.

23
00:02:02,600 --> 00:02:03,200
Qiming,

24
00:02:03,720 --> 00:02:04,720
always remember,

25
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:07,600
never do anything against our conscience.

26
00:02:09,199 --> 00:02:09,930
Up in the sky,

27
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:13,440
there are always eyes watching us.

28
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:17,160
But politics is politics,

29
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:19,240
and business is business.

30
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:21,680
Jiang Tao is here.

31
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:22,800
Jiang Tao is here.

32
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:23,840
You're here too, Ma'am.

33
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:24,680
I came to see you both.

34
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:25,010
Okay.

35
00:02:25,720 --> 00:02:27,320
You and Uncle Jiang can chat.

36
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:28,520
I'll be going now.

37
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:29,000
Okay.

38
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:31,160
Jiang Tao.

39
00:02:31,760 --> 00:02:34,020
Sir, have you been in good health lately?

40
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:34,930
Pretty good.

41
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:35,440
Look,

42
00:02:36,320 --> 00:02:37,380
I'm fit as a fiddle.

43
00:02:38,320 --> 00:02:38,920
Actually,

44
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:41,400
I wanted to come see you a couple of days ago.

45
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:42,560
You young people,

46
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:45,780
stop worrying about an old guy like me every day.

47
00:02:45,920 --> 00:02:48,320
Doing your job well is the most important thing.

48
00:02:48,320 --> 00:02:48,840
Yeah.

49
00:02:49,880 --> 00:02:51,720
There's indeed a lot going on recently,

50
00:02:51,720 --> 00:02:53,780
I wish I could be in two places at once.

51
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:56,480
Is there some problem with your work?

52
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:00,400
Sir.

53
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:02,440
You know me best.

54
00:03:03,040 --> 00:03:04,120
I came from a rural area

55
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,250
with no background,

56
00:03:05,720 --> 00:03:07,440
relying entirely on taking one step at a time

57
00:03:07,440 --> 00:03:09,100
to reach my current position.

58
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:12,720
As for the promotion,

59
00:03:13,320 --> 00:03:15,480
I really don't dare to think about it anymore.

60
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:16,940
With your working ability

61
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:18,200
and level,

62
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:19,800
you can strive for it.

63
00:03:22,040 --> 00:03:23,570
What's there to strive for?

64
00:03:24,160 --> 00:03:25,079
You don't know,

65
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:26,660
ever since I became

66
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:28,400
a reserve cadre candidate,

67
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:30,400
people have been suppressing me at every turn.

68
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:32,760
Someone even reported me for accepting bribes.

69
00:03:32,760 --> 00:03:34,280
Is this actually true?

70
00:03:35,320 --> 00:03:36,120
Sir.

71
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:38,440
Others don't know me,

72
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:39,640
but don't you know me?

73
00:03:41,040 --> 00:03:42,370
Am I that kind of person?

74
00:03:42,520 --> 00:03:43,520
Don't lose heart.

75
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:45,640
As long as you are upright,

76
00:03:45,640 --> 00:03:47,440
a straight foot is not afraid of a crooked shoe,

77
00:03:47,440 --> 00:03:49,240
and you have a clear conscience,

78
00:03:49,440 --> 00:03:51,160
I believe the Party organization

79
00:03:51,160 --> 00:03:53,220
will bring you justice and fairness.

80
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:56,450
You are my most promising student.

81
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:57,680
Yes.

82
00:03:58,440 --> 00:03:59,960
Thank you for your comforting words.

83
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:01,440
I definitely won't let you down.

84
00:04:01,440 --> 00:04:02,500
Good. That's good.

85
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:16,490
Why are you here?

86
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:18,529
Didn't I tell you to run?

87
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:20,260
I don't have enough money.

88
00:04:20,640 --> 00:04:21,970
I'm wanted everywhere.

89
00:04:23,080 --> 00:04:24,080
Where can I run to?

90
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:26,170
Are you trying to get us killed?

91
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:30,140
If you don't give me money,

92
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:31,530
I'll turn myself in.

93
00:04:34,640 --> 00:04:35,200
How much do you want?

94
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:35,930
One million.

95
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:39,280
Don't be too greedy.

96
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:40,400
Greedy?

97
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:43,320
Sister Na,

98
00:04:43,840 --> 00:04:44,770
compared to you,

99
00:04:45,520 --> 00:04:46,600
I fall far short.

100
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:49,640
Okay.

101
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:52,930
I'll go raise the money for you.

102
00:04:53,640 --> 00:04:54,480
Hide yourself quickly.

103
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:56,080
Don't let anyone find you, hear me?

104
00:04:56,080 --> 00:04:57,480
Okay, got it.

105
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:02,120
Hurry up.

106
00:05:22,760 --> 00:05:23,820
Hello, Godfather.

107
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:25,020
Chen Hao showed up.

108
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:26,440
There might be trouble.

109
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:27,500
He wants a million.

110
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:29,000
Insatiable.

111
00:05:29,560 --> 00:05:30,820
Should we take him out?

112
00:05:31,520 --> 00:05:32,720
Don't worry about it.

113
00:05:32,880 --> 00:05:35,010
Hurry up and take over Tongda Company.

114
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:36,900
I'll get someone to handle it.

115
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:37,730
Understood.

116
00:06:48,560 --> 00:06:49,040
Help me.

117
00:06:57,800 --> 00:06:58,330
Let's go.

118
00:06:58,600 --> 00:06:59,960
Thank you for your cooperation.

119
00:06:59,960 --> 00:07:01,840
This bastard swapped the steel bars.

120
00:07:01,840 --> 00:07:03,400
You have to seek justice for us.

121
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:04,760
When I was working overtime,

122
00:07:04,760 --> 00:07:06,360
I never expected to run into him.

123
00:07:06,360 --> 00:07:07,880
Our lives matter too.

124
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:09,120
We have wives at home

125
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:10,120
waiting for us.

126
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:11,530
Understood.

127
00:07:11,840 --> 00:07:13,480
He will definitely face justice.

128
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:14,080
Thank you.

129
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:15,930
Good work today.

130
00:07:21,200 --> 00:07:21,730
Let's go.

131
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:29,900
Manager Yu.

132
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:31,080
I'm late.

133
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,400
You are really not punctual.

134
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:36,320
I've been a bit busy with the case. Please excuse me.

135
00:07:36,320 --> 00:07:38,840
You said you wanted to provide clues regarding Tian Liang's case.

136
00:07:38,840 --> 00:07:39,880
I have started recording.

137
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:40,810
Please go ahead.

138
00:07:41,640 --> 00:07:42,700
Is it that serious?

139
00:07:42,840 --> 00:07:43,920
It's a disciplinary requirement.

140
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:45,050
Please understand.

141
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:51,650
Tian Liang has a house in the eastern suburbs.

142
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:53,280
It was a gift from Xia Lin.

143
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:55,159
It also belongs to Tongda Group.

144
00:07:55,159 --> 00:07:56,620
You can go and look into it.

145
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:58,409
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

146
00:07:58,960 --> 00:08:00,360
I just remembered it.

147
00:08:00,440 --> 00:08:02,170
I reported it to you right away.

148
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:04,530
I'll send the address to your phone later.

149
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:07,500
Are there any other clues?

150
00:08:08,040 --> 00:08:10,770
Not for now. I'll tell you if I remember anything.

151
00:08:12,640 --> 00:08:13,960
Thank you for your cooperation.

152
00:08:13,960 --> 00:08:16,000
Next time, you can just call me directly.

153
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:16,530
Goodbye.

154
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:22,480
According to colleagues,

155
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:24,120
the scene was cleaned very thoroughly.

156
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:25,200
There were no footprints,

157
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:26,400
and no fingerprints.

158
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:29,160
Then this person likely has a criminal record.

159
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:29,560
Right.

160
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:33,140
His anti-reconnaissance awareness is too strong.

161
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:34,200
Alright.

162
00:08:36,559 --> 00:08:37,360
What did you find?

163
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:37,799
Captain Jiang.

164
00:08:37,799 --> 00:08:38,480
Inside the house,

165
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:40,039
we found two spots with a luminol reaction.

166
00:08:40,039 --> 00:08:41,039
A small amount of blood on the sofa,

167
00:08:41,039 --> 00:08:41,919
and a large amount of blood in the bathroom.

168
00:08:41,919 --> 00:08:43,039
We have already collected the evidence.

169
00:08:43,039 --> 00:08:43,640
Thank you.

170
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:44,840
Xiao Li.

171
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:45,860
Master.

172
00:08:46,760 --> 00:08:47,620
You can come in.

173
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:54,160
Two glasses of water.

174
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:56,240
What else did you find?

175
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:58,240
Tian Liang poured water for the person who entered.

176
00:08:58,240 --> 00:09:00,800
This indicates it was highly likely committed by an acquaintance.

177
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:02,800
At the very least, it wasn't a violent break-in.

178
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:03,260
Agreed.

179
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:10,050
The fingerprints on the cup were wiped clean.

180
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:11,760
This means the killer is experienced.

181
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:14,160
And it doesn't look like a crime of passion.

182
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:16,330
It's more like a premeditated murder.

183
00:09:16,840 --> 00:09:17,840
That's possible.

184
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:20,400
But we have to wait for Mr. Jin's report.

185
00:09:21,040 --> 00:09:23,370
There is a little blood in the living room,

186
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:24,840
and a lot in the bathroom.

187
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:26,320
This indicates the living room is likely

188
00:09:26,320 --> 00:09:27,720
the primary crime scene.

189
00:09:27,880 --> 00:09:30,280
After the killer murdered Tian Liang here,

190
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:33,650
they moved him to the bathroom to dismember the body.

191
00:09:33,680 --> 00:09:34,940
Go check the bathroom.

192
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:37,580
Xiao Li, where are you?

193
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:38,130
I'm here.

194
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:48,280
Get up.

195
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:53,770
Who is it?

196
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:54,600
Delivery.

197
00:09:57,680 --> 00:09:58,960
Hello, police.

198
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:00,560
We need to ask you a few questions.

199
00:10:00,560 --> 00:10:01,560
Don't be nervous.

200
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:03,530
On the night of the 24th to the 25th,

201
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:05,520
did you hear any unusual sounds?

202
00:10:05,880 --> 00:10:07,800
Like the sound of running water, for example.

203
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:08,680
The 25th...

204
00:10:09,560 --> 00:10:10,040
Yes.

205
00:10:10,440 --> 00:10:12,100
The floor was banging loudly.

206
00:10:12,160 --> 00:10:13,560
It lasted for a long time.

207
00:10:13,840 --> 00:10:16,240
Then, there was the sound of rushing water.

208
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:20,600
Were there any other unusual sounds?

209
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:21,520
Others?

210
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:22,360
Yes.

211
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:24,120
Later, it was the sound of going up and down the stairs.

212
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:26,040
It went on for over an hour.

213
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:28,120
It was so noisy I couldn't even sleep well.

214
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:30,240
Do you remember approximately what time it was?

215
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:31,560
As for the time,

216
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:33,800
it was around 12:30 AM.

217
00:10:36,920 --> 00:10:38,650
Thank you, sorry to bother you.

218
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:40,480
Around 12:30.

219
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:41,760
We have the time.

220
00:10:41,760 --> 00:10:42,220
Xiao Li,

221
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:43,880
go find Zhao and tell Jin to hurry up.

222
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:45,010
Okay, Captain Shen.

223
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:45,840
Let's go.

224
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:47,330
Brother.

225
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:48,040
Hello.

226
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:49,000
I need to ask you something.

227
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:49,530
Go ahead.

228
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:51,320
July 24th and 25th,

229
00:10:51,520 --> 00:10:52,800
were you on the night shift?

230
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:54,440
The 24th and 25th?

231
00:10:54,480 --> 00:10:55,210
Let me check.

232
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:57,330
Yes, that's right. It was my shift.

233
00:10:57,520 --> 00:10:59,720
Around 12:30 a.m. that night,

234
00:10:59,920 --> 00:11:01,240
did you notice anything unusual?

235
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:02,400
12:30 a.m.?

236
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:03,960
There actually was something.

237
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:06,080
At 12:30 that night, a cleaner

238
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:08,200
rode a tricycle out to throw away garbage.

239
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:10,000
Our neighborhood hasn't been peaceful lately.

240
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:10,920
A resident reported

241
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:12,160
losing an electric tricycle.

242
00:11:12,160 --> 00:11:13,960
I don't know if it's the same one.

243
00:11:14,280 --> 00:11:15,760
Can we take a look at the surveillance footage?

244
00:11:15,760 --> 00:11:16,920
The surveillance? It's right in this room.

245
00:11:16,920 --> 00:11:17,720
Thank you. This way, please.

246
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:18,320
Thank you.

247
00:11:20,160 --> 00:11:21,290
Is it okay like this?

248
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:23,400
Pause.

249
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:25,040
Please zoom in for us.

250
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:30,920
Don't you restrict residents going in and out at night?

251
00:11:30,920 --> 00:11:31,920
Residents in our neighborhood

252
00:11:31,920 --> 00:11:32,840
all have blue passes to go out.

253
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:34,160
We can't restrict them.

254
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:35,800
Can you give us a copy of the surveillance footage?

255
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:36,320
Sure.

256
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:38,780
Thanks for your cooperation.

257
00:11:41,640 --> 00:11:42,320
I know.

258
00:11:42,880 --> 00:11:44,680
I'll confirm Chen Hao's crimes.

259
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:53,320
Officer.

260
00:11:55,320 --> 00:11:57,520
I am at Tongda Group's sandpit

261
00:11:57,840 --> 00:11:59,700
and found a suspicious tricycle.

262
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:03,370
Please come over and investigate.

263
00:12:08,160 --> 00:12:09,160
Sounds familiar.

264
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:10,320
Play it again.

265
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:16,330
Are we thinking the same thing?

266
00:12:17,240 --> 00:12:19,760
Voice recordings can't be used as evidence without comparison.

267
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:22,620
We still need to catch Qian Yong as soon as possible.

268
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:23,880
We just caught Chen Hao,

269
00:12:23,880 --> 00:12:25,940
and so many strange things happened.

270
00:12:26,160 --> 00:12:26,960
It's so weird.

271
00:12:27,880 --> 00:12:28,610
Don't panic.

272
00:12:30,400 --> 00:12:32,130
Let's wait for the test report.

273
00:12:53,760 --> 00:12:54,220
Tell me.

274
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:59,060
There's solid evidence that you swapped the rebar.

275
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:00,660
Who put you up to it?

276
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:05,320
Since you don't want to talk about that,

277
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:07,960
let's talk about something else.

278
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:09,490
How did you kill Tian Liang?

279
00:13:23,520 --> 00:13:25,650
Someone asked me to give you a message.

280
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:28,440
Did Yu Na send you?

281
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:30,760
Did you bring the money?

282
00:13:30,760 --> 00:13:31,760
No money, no deal.

283
00:13:36,160 --> 00:13:37,440
Your wife and kids.

284
00:13:39,680 --> 00:13:40,640
I'm warning you.

285
00:13:41,080 --> 00:13:42,340
Don't touch my family.

286
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:54,160
Can you talk now?

287
00:13:58,680 --> 00:13:59,240
Speak.

288
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:02,130
What do you want me to do?

289
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:04,320
Go in.

290
00:14:06,160 --> 00:14:07,640
After this promotion,

291
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:09,360
someone will get you out.

292
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:11,920
Remember what you said.

293
00:14:12,960 --> 00:14:14,290
And you should remember

294
00:14:14,560 --> 00:14:15,440
what to say

295
00:14:15,720 --> 00:14:16,840
and what not to say.

296
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:31,680
You don't think anyone can bail you out, do you?

297
00:14:31,880 --> 00:14:32,520
Chen Hao.

298
00:14:33,680 --> 00:14:35,480
I advise you to confess honestly

299
00:14:35,560 --> 00:14:37,080
and make amends for your crimes.

300
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:39,000
Don't fantasize that someone can bail you out now.

301
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:40,060
Do you understand?

302
00:14:40,160 --> 00:14:40,690
Chen Hao.

303
00:14:41,360 --> 00:14:43,760
Right now, only we can protect your family.

304
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:50,360
Can I have some water?

305
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:03,560
Can you talk now?

306
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:05,730
How did you kill Tian Liang?

307
00:15:06,760 --> 00:15:07,760
I didn't kill him.

308
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:10,730
When I got there,

309
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:12,730
he was already dead.

310
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:14,000
What did you say?
